article.headline: Lehigh 68, Princeton 49
article.story: BETHLEHEM, Pa. (AP) -- Zahir Carrington made all seven of his free throws and finished with 27 points to lead Lehigh to 68-49 victory over Princeton on Sunday. The Mountain Hawks snapped a 23-game losing streak against Princeton and beat the Tigers for the first time since 1930. Lehigh (7-7), which snapped a two-game losing streak, shot 58 percent (14-for-24) from the field in the first half and built a 41-19 lead by the break. Rob Keefer shot 3-for-4 from 3-point range and added 16 points for Lehigh, which outscored Princeton 18-8 in points off turnovers and converted 23 of 26 shots from the line. Nick Lake scored eight points to lead Princeton (2-11), which lost its 11th straight game after opening the season with consecutive wins. The Tigers' last win came Nov. 14 at home against Iona 66-58. Princeton shot 7-for-21 (33 percent) in the first half and 37 percent for the game. The Tigers went 2-for-4 from the line.
